#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
PyManifest UNIFIED - Complete Static + Dynamic Analysis with Self-Healing
=========================================================================
Integrated system combining versions 3, 4, and 5, with advanced pattern learning
and logical iteration. Features:

1. STATIC ANALYSIS – 6xW1H+State blueprint generation
2. RUNTIME TRACING – Call, line, exception, import, GUI widget capture
3. DIFF & COVERAGE – Compare static vs runtime, detect gaps
4. INFERENCE – Fill missing metadata (imports, types, properties)
5. HEALING – Regex traceback parsing, Levenshtein typo correction, auto‑indent
6. GUI DEBUGGING – Tkinter/Matplotlib geometry analysis
7. PREREQUISITE CHAINS – Model conditions for successful execution
8. FIX IMPACT ANALYSIS – Simulate effect of fixes on existing traces
9. HARD CALCULATION – Z3‑based constraint verification (optional)
10. SAFETY VERIFICATION – Only apply fixes that pass no‑regression
11. PATTERN LEARNING – SHA‑hash successful execution patterns; reuse across runs
12. LOGICAL ITERATION – Variable workflows; try‑revert‑retry with learned patterns

All results are merged into a single evolving manifest (state.json) with full
6xW1H traceability.

Author: Bradly Aish
Dependencies (optional): networkx, matplotlib, autopep8, black, Levenshtein, z3-solver, tkinter
"""

